        "action": "Equal rights for Fathers-to-be to be paid leave for antenatal appointments.",
        "additional_details": "Statutory Paternity Pay and Leave: employer guide:-\r\nhttps://www.gov.uk/employers-paternity-pay-leave\r\n\r\nPregnant employees' rights:-\r\nhttps://www.gov.uk/working-when-pregnant-your-rights\r\n\r\nEquality Act 2010:-\r\nhttps://www.gov.uk/guidance/equality-act-2010-guidance",
        "background": "In a society where equal rights matter, I believe Fathers-to-be should be allowed the same right as the Mother-to-be. This is the right of paid time off for antenatal care, of which equally includes antenatal or parenting classes if they\u2019ve been recommended by a doctor or midwife.",
